text: Soini is a municipality in Southern Ostrobothnia, Finland. It had about 2,300 living there in January 2014. The municipalities next to it are Alajärvi, Karstula, Kyyjärvi, Saarijärvi and Ähtäri. The municipality was established in 1868. == Other websites == * Page Category:1868 establishments in Finland Category:Municipalities of South Ostrobothnia
